The paper deals with unsupervised clustering of two-way (matrix) data using an algebraic approach. The paper uses Sparse Subspace Clustering (SSC) algorithm and t-product to cluster the data. The paper also discusses the use of free modules over a commutative ring to embed the 2-D data into a vector-space-like structure. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of convolutions and theoretical guarantees, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
